1
00:00:01,141 --> 00:00:03,349
<i>[Narrator] Alchemy:</i>
<i>the science of understanding,</i>

2
00:00:03,349 --> 00:00:05,749
<i>deconstructing, and</i>
<i>reconstructing matter.</i>

3
00:00:05,782 --> 00:00:08,616
<i>However, it is not</i>
<i>an all-powerful art.</i>

4
00:00:08,649 --> 00:00:11,582
<i>It is impossible to create</i>
<i>something out of nothing.</i>

5
00:00:11,616 --> 00:00:13,516
<i>If one wishes to</i>
<i>obtain something,</i>

6
00:00:13,549 --> 00:00:16,116
<i>something of equal</i>
<i>value must be given.</i>

7
00:00:16,149 --> 00:00:18,549
<i>This is the Law of</i>
<i>Equivalent Exchange.</i>

8
00:00:18,582 --> 00:00:20,482
<i>The basis of all alchemy.</i>

9
00:00:20,516 --> 00:00:22,049
<i>In accordance with this law,</i>

10
00:00:22,082 --> 00:00:23,782
<i>there is a taboo</i>
<i>among alchemists.</i>

11
00:00:23,816 --> 00:00:26,282
<i>Human transmutation</i>
<i>is strictly forbidden.</i>

12
00:00:26,316 --> 00:00:29,316
<i>For what could equal</i>
<i>the value of a human soul?</i>

13
00:02:03,116 --> 00:02:06,076
<i>[Narrator] The town of Liore</i>
<i>had fallen under the control</i>

14
00:02:06,076 --> 00:02:09,476
<i>of Father Cornello, a corrupt</i>
<i>priest who used alchemy</i>

15
00:02:09,509 --> 00:02:12,776
<i>combined with a Philosopher's</i>
<i>Stone to deceive his people.</i>

16
00:02:12,809 --> 00:02:15,042
<i>Ed and Al came to</i>
<i>Liore and put a stop</i>

17
00:02:15,076 --> 00:02:17,009
to the priest's sinister plans.

18
00:02:17,042 --> 00:02:18,776
<i>The Philospher's</i>
<i>Stone, however,</i>

19
00:02:18,809 --> 00:02:20,509
<i>was revealed to be a fake.</i>

20
00:02:20,542 --> 00:02:22,442
Their leader exposed as a fraud,

21
00:02:22,476 --> 00:02:25,009
<i>the hopes of the citizens</i>
<i>of Liore were crushed.</i>

22
00:02:25,042 --> 00:02:27,609
<i>"Stand up and walk.</i>
<i>Move forward."</i>

23
00:02:27,642 --> 00:02:29,776
These were Ed's words to Rose--

24
00:02:29,809 --> 00:02:32,376
<i>words he had once</i>
<i>needed to hear himself.</i>

25
00:02:38,809 --> 00:02:41,042
[footsteps]

26
00:02:44,176 --> 00:02:47,909
[Scar] You are Basque Grand, the
Iron Blood Alchemist... correct?

27
00:02:47,942 --> 00:02:50,442
[Grand] Why? Who's asking?

28
00:02:50,476 --> 00:02:53,009
Foolish alchemists who have
turned their backs on the

29
00:02:53,042 --> 00:02:55,942
ways of God...
shall all be punished.

30
00:02:55,976 --> 00:02:58,609
I see... You must be
the bloodthirsty murderer

31
00:02:58,642 --> 00:03:00,009
who's been making
a habit of targeting

32
00:03:00,042 --> 00:03:02,109
State Alchemists lately...

33
00:03:02,142 --> 00:03:03,509
[clanging metal]
ker-clang

34
00:03:03,542 --> 00:03:04,142
[magic shimmer]

35
00:03:04,176 --> 00:03:05,609
Well this time...

36
00:03:05,642 --> 00:03:06,876
...you've picked
the wrong target!

37
00:03:06,909 --> 00:03:08,909
[electroshock bolts]
kazzzurghzzzzzch

38
00:03:09,776 --> 00:03:11,476
Yerrrr-agh!

39
00:03:11,509 --> 00:03:12,476
[wizardly hum]

40
00:03:12,509 --> 00:03:13,376
[earthy explosion]
crumBLAM

41
00:03:13,409 --> 00:03:15,009
[cannon blasts]
bang bang ba-bang bang

42
00:03:16,742 --> 00:03:17,842
[explosions]

43
00:03:18,542 --> 00:03:20,676
You're fast. Try this!

44
00:03:20,709 --> 00:03:21,609
[electrobolts]

45
00:03:21,642 --> 00:03:22,476
[electrochains]

46
00:03:22,509 --> 00:03:23,676
[running footsteps]

47
00:03:23,709 --> 00:03:24,909
A little more?

48
00:03:24,942 --> 00:03:26,009
[earthy magic hum]

49
00:03:26,042 --> 00:03:26,809
[metallic crash]

50
00:03:28,842 --> 00:03:31,809
Hmph...
That wasn't so difficult.

51
00:03:31,842 --> 00:03:33,876
[footsteps]

52
00:03:37,876 --> 00:03:38,576
Huh?

53
00:03:38,609 --> 00:03:39,642
[explosion]

54
00:03:41,142 --> 00:03:43,742
[Grand]
What?! No! How?!

55
00:03:43,776 --> 00:03:44,842
Now you perish.

56
00:03:44,876 --> 00:03:45,742
[harsh electroshocks]

57
00:03:45,776 --> 00:03:47,809
[splash explosion]

58
00:03:47,842 --> 00:03:49,042
[thud]
ker-thud

59
00:03:57,176 --> 00:04:00,109
[Hughes]
Another State Alchemist dead?

60
00:04:00,142 --> 00:04:02,142
[Armstrong]
This killer is highly skilled.

61
00:04:02,176 --> 00:04:04,742
[Hughes]
Major, you watch yourself.

62
00:04:04,776 --> 00:04:07,909
For all we know, you could be
the next one he comes after.

63
00:04:07,942 --> 00:04:09,076
Understood.

64
00:04:09,109 --> 00:04:10,742
[car tires squealing]

65
00:04:15,642 --> 00:04:16,976
Fuhrer Bradley,
Your Excellency.

66
00:04:17,009 --> 00:04:18,809
What brings you here?

67
00:04:18,842 --> 00:04:20,676
[footsteps]

68
00:04:20,709 --> 00:04:23,009
[Bradley]
I got word of what happened.

69
00:04:23,042 --> 00:04:24,542
Lieutenant Colonel Hughes,

70
00:04:24,576 --> 00:04:26,442
you're the officer
in charge of this case?

71
00:04:26,476 --> 00:04:27,576
Yes sir.

72
00:04:27,609 --> 00:04:30,676
Should you need any
additional personnel, just ask.

73
00:04:30,709 --> 00:04:35,009
The man doing this is
a traitor. I want him stopped.

74
00:04:35,742 --> 00:04:36,642
Sir.

75
00:04:36,676 --> 00:04:38,942
[birds chriping]
chee-chirp chee-chee-chirp

76
00:04:39,942 --> 00:04:41,676
Lieutenant Breda.

77
00:04:41,709 --> 00:04:44,109
Right... Jeez...

78
00:04:44,142 --> 00:04:47,642
The Colonel's sure letting his
work pile up again, huh?

79
00:04:47,676 --> 00:04:50,076
Havoc... gimme a hand, will ya?

80
00:04:50,109 --> 00:04:52,742
I've got plenty to do
over here already.

81
00:04:52,776 --> 00:04:55,076
[Havoc] Next up... Who's this?

82
00:04:55,109 --> 00:04:56,709
[Falman] Lieutenant Yoki.

83
00:04:56,742 --> 00:04:59,542
Remember, the crook who was
using the Youswell coal mine

84
00:04:59,576 --> 00:05:01,742
concessions to line
his own pockets?

85
00:05:01,776 --> 00:05:03,476
Anyway, the Elric
brothers exposed

86
00:05:03,509 --> 00:05:04,876
what that dirty
thief was up to,

87
00:05:04,909 --> 00:05:06,109
and now he's on the run.

88
00:05:06,809 --> 00:05:09,142
[Hawkeye] Master Sergeant
Fuery, how's the radio?

89
00:05:09,176 --> 00:05:11,642
The receiver on this
thing's seen better days.

90
00:05:11,676 --> 00:05:13,409
I think I'm gonna
have to replace it.

91
00:05:13,442 --> 00:05:14,409
[magical hum]

92
00:05:14,442 --> 00:05:16,142
[electricity]
sssszerk

93
00:05:16,176 --> 00:05:17,042
Huh?

94
00:05:17,076 --> 00:05:19,709
[Fuery] Hey, it's
Edward and Alphonse!

95
00:05:19,742 --> 00:05:20,542
[Hawkeye] Welcome back boys...

96
00:05:20,576 --> 00:05:23,009
Go on in, the Colonel's
expecting you.

97
00:05:23,042 --> 00:05:24,042
[groan]

98
00:05:25,176 --> 00:05:27,809
Well done on the Liore case,
you two. Nice work...

99
00:05:27,842 --> 00:05:29,676
I appreciate you
resolving the matter.

100
00:05:29,709 --> 00:05:32,176
No big deal.
It's not like we did it for you.

101
00:05:32,209 --> 00:05:34,509
[Roy] Right.
The Philosopher's Stone.

102
00:05:34,542 --> 00:05:36,042
Another false lead?

103
00:05:39,809 --> 00:05:41,709
Yeah, after all that,
the stone was a fake.

104
00:05:41,742 --> 00:05:45,476
Even so... the power it gave
Cornello was real enough.

105
00:05:45,509 --> 00:05:48,042
He transmuted this huge
chimera right in front of us.

106
00:05:48,076 --> 00:05:49,876
[Al] I still wonder how
he was able to use

107
00:05:49,909 --> 00:05:52,576
the stone to do that.
I'm not familiar enough

108
00:05:52,609 --> 00:05:55,409
with the field of bio-alchemy
to really understand it.

109
00:05:55,442 --> 00:05:57,509
Yeah, I'm kind of curious
about that to...

110
00:05:57,542 --> 00:06:00,809
It might be worth looking into.
Who knows, maybe we'll find

111
00:06:00,842 --> 00:06:02,742
something that could help
us restore our bodies.

112
00:06:02,776 --> 00:06:03,676
[Al] Hmm.

113
00:06:03,709 --> 00:06:05,976
It might help if you
consulted a specialist.

114
00:06:06,009 --> 00:06:07,142
[Both] Huh?

115
00:06:08,376 --> 00:06:10,909
[Roy] The Sewing Life Alchemist,
Shou Tucker... He's done some

116
00:06:10,942 --> 00:06:13,076
heavy research into
chimera transmutation.

117
00:06:13,109 --> 00:06:14,076
I'll introduce you.

118
00:06:14,109 --> 00:06:16,142
[Al] You would do
that for us?

119
00:06:16,176 --> 00:06:18,642
Okay, what's the catch! You want
something, don't you!

120
00:06:18,676 --> 00:06:21,009
[Roy] Don't doubt my motives!
I'm trying to repay you

121
00:06:21,042 --> 00:06:22,942
for your work on
the Liore case.

122
00:06:22,976 --> 00:06:26,376
Doing you a favor is better
than being indebted to you.

123
00:06:27,776 --> 00:06:30,609
<i>[Roy] Two years ago, Tucker</i>
<i>transmuted a chimera that</i>

124
00:06:30,642 --> 00:06:32,876
<i>could understand human</i>
<i>speech. That earned him</i>

125
00:06:32,909 --> 00:06:34,809
<i>his certification as</i>
<i>a State Alchemist.</i>

126
00:06:34,842 --> 00:06:36,876
By "understand human
speech," you mean...

127
00:06:36,909 --> 00:06:39,809
Wait, You mean it talks?
A chimera?!

128
00:06:39,842 --> 00:06:42,609
Right... supposedly.

129
00:06:42,642 --> 00:06:44,609
It only said one thing.

130
00:06:44,642 --> 00:06:47,976
[Roy] "I want to die."

131
00:06:48,009 --> 00:06:49,142
[gasp]

132
00:06:49,176 --> 00:06:52,976
[Roy] After that, it refused to
eat until it got its wish.

133
00:06:55,411 --> 00:06:56,811
[bell ringing]

134
00:06:58,624 --> 00:07:00,904
[Ed] Man, this house is huge!

135
00:07:00,904 --> 00:07:02,004
[swoosh]

136
00:07:02,038 --> 00:07:03,838
[slomo barking]

137
00:07:03,871 --> 00:07:05,371
[Ed, screaming]

138
00:07:05,404 --> 00:07:07,104
[Al] You okay, Ed?

139
00:07:07,138 --> 00:07:09,004
[Nina] Daddy!

140
00:07:09,038 --> 00:07:11,238
There are people
out here! Look.

141
00:07:11,271 --> 00:07:14,838
Nina... this is why I told
you to keep the dog tied up.

142
00:07:14,871 --> 00:07:15,971
[spring sound]
boy-oy-oing

143
00:07:18,038 --> 00:07:20,404
[Tucker] I'm sorry about
the mess. Ever since my wife

144
00:07:20,438 --> 00:07:22,704
ran out, this place
has been a wreck.

145
00:07:22,738 --> 00:07:24,838
I'm not much of a housekeeper.

146
00:07:29,171 --> 00:07:30,204
[sighs]

147
00:07:30,238 --> 00:07:32,138
Now that we're all settled
in, let me say that it's

148
00:07:32,171 --> 00:07:34,738
a pleasure to meet you, Edward.
As the colonel told you,

149
00:07:34,771 --> 00:07:36,938
I'm the Sewing Life Alchemist,
Shou Tucker.

150
00:07:36,971 --> 00:07:40,104
Ed is interested in the field
of biologic alchemy.

151
00:07:40,138 --> 00:07:41,738
He would like to have a
look at your research

152
00:07:41,771 --> 00:07:42,938
if that's possible.

153
00:07:42,971 --> 00:07:45,138
Oh yes, certainly,
I don't mind.

154
00:07:46,338 --> 00:07:47,404
However...

155
00:07:47,438 --> 00:07:48,604
[armor clank, gasp]

156
00:07:48,638 --> 00:07:51,204
If you want me to show you the
tricks I've got up my sleeve,

157
00:07:51,238 --> 00:07:52,838
it's only fair that
you show me the tricks

158
00:07:52,871 --> 00:07:54,671
you've got up yours as well.

159
00:07:54,704 --> 00:07:57,238
[Tucker] It's the code we
live by--equivalent exchange.

160
00:07:57,271 --> 00:08:00,738
Now. Why are you
interested in bio-alchemy?

161
00:08:00,771 --> 00:08:03,071
Oh, um... Ed...
Well, you see, he's--

162
00:08:03,104 --> 00:08:04,171
Colonel.

163
00:08:04,404 --> 00:08:05,771
[birds chirping]
chee-chee chee-chirp

164
00:08:07,338 --> 00:08:10,138
[Tucker]
You transmuted your mother...

165
00:08:10,171 --> 00:08:12,171
...as an eleven-year-old child?

166
00:08:13,204 --> 00:08:15,738
[Tucker] I see...
So that's what earned you

167
00:08:15,771 --> 00:08:18,138
the title 'Fullmetal Alchemist.'

168
00:08:18,171 --> 00:08:21,004
You've had a rough time
of it for someone so young.

169
00:08:26,038 --> 00:08:27,804
I can't say for sure
if it's going to be

170
00:08:27,838 --> 00:08:30,004
of any use to
you or not...

171
00:08:30,038 --> 00:08:32,738
[Tucker]
But why don't you go ahead and
take a look at my laboratory.

172
00:08:32,771 --> 00:08:33,871
[weird animal sounds]

173
00:08:34,471 --> 00:08:35,938
[roaring and growling]
rrrrrro, grrrrrrwl

174
00:08:36,704 --> 00:08:38,004
[more weird animal sounds]

175
00:08:38,771 --> 00:08:40,738
[Tucker] It's kind
of embarrassing.

176
00:08:40,771 --> 00:08:43,971
I'm fairly widely regarded
as an authority on chimeras.

177
00:08:44,004 --> 00:08:45,404
But the truth is...

178
00:08:45,438 --> 00:08:48,038
It hasn't actually been
going that well lately.

179
00:08:48,071 --> 00:08:49,671
[door creaks opening]

180
00:08:51,104 --> 00:08:53,004
[Ed] Ohh... Amazing!

181
00:08:53,038 --> 00:08:55,371
[Tucker] This is my library.
Feel free to look around.

182
00:08:55,404 --> 00:08:58,238
All right, then let's dive in!
I'll start with this shelf!

183
00:08:58,271 --> 00:09:00,138
[Al] I'll try starting
over here.

184
00:09:01,804 --> 00:09:03,771
I'm going to head
back to work now.

185
00:09:03,804 --> 00:09:06,204
I'll send somebody by
to get you this evening.

186
00:09:08,438 --> 00:09:09,704
[scoffing]

187
00:09:09,738 --> 00:09:11,738
They've got some
ability to focus,

188
00:09:11,771 --> 00:09:14,138
I'm not sure they even
know we're here anymore.

189
00:09:14,171 --> 00:09:20,038
Quite a catch, these two...
A couple of prodigies.

190
00:09:21,271 --> 00:09:23,671
[clock ticking]

191
00:09:31,304 --> 00:09:32,138
[Al] Hmm?

192
00:09:32,171 --> 00:09:33,138
[gasp]

193
00:09:33,171 --> 00:09:35,004
[running footsteps]

194
00:09:35,038 --> 00:09:37,671
♪ Playful Music ♪

195
00:09:37,704 --> 00:09:38,771
[giggles]

196
00:09:40,138 --> 00:09:44,904
[childlike laughter]

197
00:09:45,004 --> 00:09:47,238
[Al] Woo-hoo! Way up high!

198
00:09:47,271 --> 00:09:48,371
[both laughing]

199
00:09:48,404 --> 00:09:49,671
Al, what're
you doing?!

200
00:09:49,704 --> 00:09:51,838
You're supposed
to be reading!

201
00:09:51,871 --> 00:09:54,004
[Al] Um.. Nina looked
like she wanted to play.

202
00:09:54,038 --> 00:09:55,271
Well, in case you forgot,

203
00:09:55,304 --> 00:09:57,738
we didn't come here
to play horsie!

204
00:09:57,771 --> 00:09:59,071
[slomo barking]

205
00:09:59,104 --> 00:10:00,838
[Ed, screaming]

206
00:10:02,704 --> 00:10:05,238
Alexander says that
he wants to play, too!

207
00:10:06,871 --> 00:10:09,071
That's what you want is it?

208
00:10:09,104 --> 00:10:12,738
You've bested me twice, dog...
But playtime is over!

209
00:10:12,771 --> 00:10:15,871
I will not lose this time.
I, Edward Elric, will use my

210
00:10:15,904 --> 00:10:17,738
considerable powers
to vanquish you!

211
00:10:17,771 --> 00:10:20,738
[Ed] You mangy mutt!

212
00:10:20,771 --> 00:10:22,704
[laughs]

213
00:10:23,771 --> 00:10:26,204
[Havoc] Hey, chief.
Your ride has arrived.

214
00:10:26,238 --> 00:10:28,304
[panting, happy whimpering]

215
00:10:28,338 --> 00:10:30,738
[Havoc] What're you up
to down there, Ed?

216
00:10:30,771 --> 00:10:33,138
Oh, uh... let's just say
I'm taking a break from

217
00:10:33,171 --> 00:10:34,671
a long day of research.

218
00:10:35,271 --> 00:10:37,771
After all that,
you must be dog tired.

219
00:10:37,804 --> 00:10:38,771
[dog whimper]

220
00:10:38,804 --> 00:10:41,404
[laughs] Why don't you
come on back tomorrow?

221
00:10:41,438 --> 00:10:43,738
You're really going
to come again?

222
00:10:43,771 --> 00:10:45,371
We'll play some more
tomorrow, okay, Nina?

223
00:10:45,404 --> 00:10:46,238
'Kay!

224
00:10:48,271 --> 00:10:50,138
[Havoc] Oh, Mister
Tucker, I almost forgot.

225
00:10:50,171 --> 00:10:51,671
I've got a message for you.

226
00:10:51,704 --> 00:10:53,038
It's from the Colonel. He says

227
00:10:53,071 --> 00:10:55,404
"Don't forget, assessment
day is coming soon."

228
00:10:55,438 --> 00:10:58,838
Yes... please assure him I know.

229
00:10:58,871 --> 00:11:00,204
Right.

230
00:11:01,804 --> 00:11:03,071
[door creaks shut]

231
00:11:06,204 --> 00:11:08,371
[Nina] Hey, Daddy?

232
00:11:08,404 --> 00:11:10,971
What does 'assessment day' mean?

233
00:11:13,438 --> 00:11:16,138
[Tucker] State alchemists have
to report on their research

234
00:11:16,171 --> 00:11:18,904
once a year in order to
keep their certification.

235
00:11:20,304 --> 00:11:21,871
You see, last year, Nina,

236
00:11:21,904 --> 00:11:24,304
your Daddy didn't get
a very good evaluation.

237
00:11:24,338 --> 00:11:27,004
Unless I do something really
impressive this year,

238
00:11:27,038 --> 00:11:29,238
I won't be a state
alchemist anymore.

239
00:11:29,271 --> 00:11:32,304
Huh? No! You'll do
just fine Daddy!

240
00:11:32,338 --> 00:11:35,338
I know you will! You're
always studying so much!

241
00:11:35,371 --> 00:11:36,738
[laughs nervously]

242
00:11:36,771 --> 00:11:39,904
You're right, Nina.
I have to try hard.

243
00:11:42,104 --> 00:11:45,904
<i>[Tucker] Or we'll be left</i>
<i>with nothing... again.</i>

244
00:11:45,938 --> 00:11:47,938
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

245
00:11:51,325 --> 00:11:53,525
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Fullmetal Alchemist.</i>

246
00:11:53,559 --> 00:11:55,092
♪ Sentimental Music ♪

247
00:11:55,125 --> 00:11:56,525
[birds chirping]

248
00:11:56,559 --> 00:11:59,125
[Al] Your mother left
two years ago?

249
00:11:59,159 --> 00:12:02,925
[Nina] Daddy said she went back
to live at her parents' house.

250
00:12:02,959 --> 00:12:05,292
[Al] It must get kind of lonely
with just you and your dad

251
00:12:05,325 --> 00:12:07,559
living in this
big house, huh?

252
00:12:07,592 --> 00:12:09,459
Nu-uh, not really...

253
00:12:09,492 --> 00:12:13,392
Daddy's so nice, and plus, I've
got Alexander to play with, too!

254
00:12:14,592 --> 00:12:18,792
But lately Daddy's been studying
in his lab all the time...

255
00:12:18,825 --> 00:12:21,825
I guess that does make
me a little bit lonely.

256
00:12:28,359 --> 00:12:29,292
[yawn]

257
00:12:29,325 --> 00:12:31,859
My shoulders
are killing me!

258
00:12:31,892 --> 00:12:34,159
[Alphonse] Maybe you should try
to move around some, Brother.

259
00:12:34,192 --> 00:12:37,792
Yeah, not a bad idea, Al...
Hey, you mangy mutt!

260
00:12:37,825 --> 00:12:38,725
[dog bark]
Rooouuughr

261
00:12:38,759 --> 00:12:41,192
Looks like you could
use some exercise.

262
00:12:41,225 --> 00:12:43,225
[Al] Let's go too, Nina!

263
00:12:44,925 --> 00:12:46,025
[laughing]

264
00:12:46,059 --> 00:12:47,425
♪ Goofy Happy Piano ♪

265
00:12:47,459 --> 00:12:50,459
[Edward and Nina
yelling happily]

266
00:12:54,359 --> 00:12:57,359
[Edward] I'm gonna get you!
Look out here I come!

267
00:12:59,825 --> 00:13:03,825
[silly music and laughing]

268
00:13:12,892 --> 00:13:15,892
<i>[Havoc] Don't forget...</i>
<i>Assessment Day is coming soon.</i>

269
00:13:23,892 --> 00:13:25,059
<i>[Hughes] What I want to</i>
<i>know is why this guy</i>

270
00:13:25,092 --> 00:13:28,859
<i>is only targeting State</i>
<i>Alchemists and no one else.</i>

271
00:13:28,892 --> 00:13:30,459
<i>If it's the military</i>
<i>he's trying to hurt,</i>

272
00:13:30,492 --> 00:13:33,092
<i>he could go after</i>
<i>normal soldiers.</i>

273
00:13:33,125 --> 00:13:35,059
<i>Surely soldiers would</i>
<i>be easier to kill</i>

274
00:13:35,092 --> 00:13:36,825
than highly skilled alchemists.

275
00:13:36,859 --> 00:13:39,259
<i>Especially ones who have</i>
<i>been state certified.</i>

276
00:13:40,125 --> 00:13:43,059
[Armstrong] Maybe the
certification is the reason.

277
00:13:43,092 --> 00:13:46,359
State Alchemists are given
high pay and special privilege.

278
00:13:46,392 --> 00:13:47,925
There must be any
number of people

279
00:13:47,959 --> 00:13:51,059
who envy them their
positions... Or, perhaps...

280
00:13:51,092 --> 00:13:52,959
...they feel they have
not upheld their creed:

281
00:13:52,992 --> 00:13:54,892
"Alchemist, be thou
for the people."

282
00:13:54,925 --> 00:13:57,825
Alchemists, who are supposed to
be pillars of science and truth,

283
00:13:57,859 --> 00:13:59,825
are turned into the
military's walking weapons

284
00:13:59,859 --> 00:14:02,825
as soon as they
receive certification.

285
00:14:02,859 --> 00:14:05,792
There are plenty of people,
I'm sure, who have not forgotten

286
00:14:05,825 --> 00:14:07,325
the role that State
Alchemists played

287
00:14:07,359 --> 00:14:09,125
in the Ishvalan Civil War.

288
00:14:09,159 --> 00:14:11,159
[knock at the door]

289
00:14:11,592 --> 00:14:13,192
I have a report, sir.

290
00:14:13,225 --> 00:14:14,992
A canvas has revealed
that yesterday,

291
00:14:15,025 --> 00:14:17,459
at nine thirty...
or right around that time,

292
00:14:17,492 --> 00:14:19,925
a man with a large scar on
his face was sighted in

293
00:14:19,959 --> 00:14:22,959
the Central City Train Station
by multiple station employees.

294
00:14:22,992 --> 00:14:24,192
The Station?

295
00:14:24,225 --> 00:14:26,459
Looks like that
bastard got away.

296
00:14:26,492 --> 00:14:28,892
♪ Melancholy Music ♪

297
00:14:28,925 --> 00:14:31,192
Before I earned my State
Alchemist certification,

298
00:14:31,225 --> 00:14:32,492
our life was terrible.

299
00:14:33,392 --> 00:14:36,259
We were so poor in those days.

300
00:14:36,292 --> 00:14:39,292
My wife couldn't stand
living that kind of life...

301
00:14:39,325 --> 00:14:41,325
...so she left us.

302
00:14:43,492 --> 00:14:46,792
I can't afford to
fail this assessment.

303
00:14:46,825 --> 00:14:48,792
I don't ever want to go
back to those days again.

304
00:14:48,825 --> 00:14:50,025
I don't even think I could.

305
00:14:50,059 --> 00:14:52,059
Don't worry, Daddy,
it's okay...

306
00:14:52,092 --> 00:14:54,059
If those people
do tell you no,

307
00:14:54,092 --> 00:14:57,059
me and Alexander will growl
at them until they say yes!

308
00:14:57,092 --> 00:15:00,792
[Alphonse, laughing]
You tell 'em, Nina!

309
00:15:00,825 --> 00:15:02,925
Hey, Nina... I've got an idea.

310
00:15:02,959 --> 00:15:04,559
Do you want to play
with Daddy tomorrow?

311
00:15:04,592 --> 00:15:06,192
Really?

312
00:15:06,225 --> 00:15:07,259
Yeah.

313
00:15:07,292 --> 00:15:09,325
Woo-hoo!

314
00:15:09,359 --> 00:15:13,192
Alexander, Daddy says he's
going to play with us tomorrow!

315
00:15:13,225 --> 00:15:14,492
[dog bark]

316
00:15:17,192 --> 00:15:19,192
[bell ringing]
ding da-ding ding

317
00:15:24,225 --> 00:15:26,159
[Al] Hello, Mr. Tucker!

318
00:15:26,192 --> 00:15:29,059
Thanks for having
us again today!

319
00:15:29,092 --> 00:15:30,092
Huh?

320
00:15:31,825 --> 00:15:33,159
[Al] Mr. Tucker?

321
00:15:33,192 --> 00:15:35,192
[Ed] Hey! Nina?!

322
00:15:37,959 --> 00:15:39,159
[Al] Mr. Tucker!

323
00:15:39,192 --> 00:15:41,992
[Ed] There you are.
So you are home!

324
00:15:42,025 --> 00:15:43,292
Yes.

325
00:15:44,025 --> 00:15:47,459
I did it boys.
I finally did it.

326
00:15:47,492 --> 00:15:50,525
A chimera that understands
human speech.

327
00:15:50,559 --> 00:15:52,925
[thunder clap]

328
00:15:52,959 --> 00:15:55,025
Here, let me show you.

329
00:15:55,059 --> 00:15:58,492
Listen to me... That person
over there, that's Edward.

330
00:15:58,525 --> 00:16:01,425
That person...
Ed... ward.

331
00:16:01,459 --> 00:16:04,025
Yes, that's very good.
Well done.

332
00:16:04,059 --> 00:16:06,925
That's amazing!
It can actually talk.

333
00:16:06,959 --> 00:16:11,925
Now I don't have to worry
about losing my certification.

334
00:16:11,959 --> 00:16:14,492
That person... Ed... ward.

335
00:16:17,192 --> 00:16:23,125
That person... Ed... ward.
That person... Ed... ward.

336
00:16:23,159 --> 00:16:25,392
Big Brother Ed.

337
00:16:30,859 --> 00:16:32,859
[thunder clap]

338
00:16:34,592 --> 00:16:35,625
[Ed] Mr. Tucker...

339
00:16:35,659 --> 00:16:38,959
When did you first get
your state certification?

340
00:16:38,992 --> 00:16:43,359
Let's see...
It was two years ago.

341
00:16:43,392 --> 00:16:47,059
[Ed] And when did
your wife leave you?

342
00:16:47,092 --> 00:16:49,325
That was two years ago, too.

343
00:16:49,359 --> 00:16:52,159
[Ed] I just have one more
question for you...

344
00:16:52,192 --> 00:16:55,959
Nina and Alexander...
Where are they?!

345
00:16:56,225 --> 00:16:58,225
♪ Menacing Music ♪

346
00:16:59,925 --> 00:17:02,192
Damn brat, figuring it
out so quickly!

347
00:17:03,992 --> 00:17:05,059
[Al] Brother!

348
00:17:05,092 --> 00:17:08,825
[Ed] Oh yeah, I figured
it out. You did it again!

349
00:17:08,859 --> 00:17:10,925
Two years ago,
it was your wife!

350
00:17:10,959 --> 00:17:13,925
This time you used your
own daughter and her dog

351
00:17:13,959 --> 00:17:15,925
to transmute a talking chimera!

352
00:17:15,959 --> 00:17:19,059
You can only do so much
with animals, after all.

353
00:17:19,092 --> 00:17:22,359
It's much easier when you start
with a human, isn't that right?!

354
00:17:22,392 --> 00:17:25,259
I don't see what you're
so upset about...

355
00:17:25,292 --> 00:17:27,325
This is how we progress.

356
00:17:27,359 --> 00:17:30,525
Human experimentation
is a necessary step.

357
00:17:30,559 --> 00:17:33,059
I would think a scientist
should understand.

358
00:17:33,092 --> 00:17:34,059
[Ed] Shut up!

359
00:17:34,092 --> 00:17:36,792
Do you really think you
can get away with this?!

360
00:17:36,825 --> 00:17:39,092
Messing around with
someone's life like that?

361
00:17:39,125 --> 00:17:40,959
Your own daughter?!

362
00:17:40,992 --> 00:17:42,392
Someone's life, you say?

363
00:17:42,425 --> 00:17:45,925
Ha ha. You'd know all
about that, wouldn't you?

364
00:17:45,959 --> 00:17:47,892
Look at you,
Fullmetal Alchemist...

365
00:17:47,925 --> 00:17:50,925
Look at your leg,
your arm, your brother!

366
00:17:50,959 --> 00:17:53,459
Those things are also the
result of messing around

367
00:17:53,492 --> 00:17:56,059
with somebody's
life, aren't they?

368
00:17:56,092 --> 00:17:58,092
[Ed] Shut up!

369
00:17:59,525 --> 00:18:02,059
[laughing]
We are the same!

370
00:18:02,092 --> 00:18:04,092
We're the same...
you're just like me!

371
00:18:04,125 --> 00:18:05,092
We're not!

372
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:06,792
Oh, but yes we are..

373
00:18:06,825 --> 00:18:09,192
The opportunity was right in
front of us, and we took it!

374
00:18:09,225 --> 00:18:12,292
We had to, even though we knew
it was against the rules.

375
00:18:12,325 --> 00:18:14,325
No!

376
00:18:14,425 --> 00:18:16,025
Not me!

377
00:18:16,059 --> 00:18:18,059
Alchemists don't...

378
00:18:18,492 --> 00:18:19,959
...do that!

379
00:18:20,925 --> 00:18:23,792
I'm not... I'm not!

380
00:18:23,825 --> 00:18:25,192
[Al] Brother!

381
00:18:25,225 --> 00:18:27,959
If you keep this up, he'll die.

382
00:18:38,292 --> 00:18:40,492
Edward... No.

383
00:18:41,425 --> 00:18:46,425
Daddy, do you... hurt? Daddy?

384
00:18:52,425 --> 00:18:55,992
[Al] I'm sorry.
Even with all our power,

385
00:18:56,025 --> 00:18:59,859
we can't do anything
to change you back.

386
00:18:59,892 --> 00:19:03,159
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

387
00:19:03,192 --> 00:19:07,325
Can we play... now?
Can we play now?

388
00:19:07,359 --> 00:19:09,559
I made it just in time...

389
00:19:09,592 --> 00:19:13,092
I get to remain a State
Alchemist. I passed!

390
00:19:24,859 --> 00:19:28,859
[Ed]
Like hell, you're staying a
State Alchemist! Like hell!

391
00:19:30,359 --> 00:19:33,359
Can we... play now?

392
00:19:35,259 --> 00:19:38,259
[Ed screams]

393
00:19:38,992 --> 00:19:40,992
[rain falling]

394
00:19:41,959 --> 00:19:44,059
<i>[Hawkeye] If ever there was</i>
<i>an example of the devil's</i>

395
00:19:44,092 --> 00:19:48,059
<i>work in this world, this case</i>
<i>would definitely be it.</i>

396
00:19:48,092 --> 00:19:50,192
<i>[Roy] The devil, huh?</i>

397
00:19:50,225 --> 00:19:52,925
<i>A State Alchemist</i>
<i>must be willing to act,</i>

398
00:19:52,959 --> 00:19:56,925
able to take another's life when
ordered to without questioning.

399
00:19:56,959 --> 00:19:58,159
<i>In some ways,</i>

400
00:19:58,192 --> 00:20:02,325
Mr. Tucker's actions and our own
may not be all that far apart,

401
00:20:02,359 --> 00:20:05,292
<i>when it comes to interfering</i>
<i>with other people's lives.</i>

402
00:20:05,325 --> 00:20:08,925
We choose our own path, knowing
full well what we're doing.

403
00:20:11,159 --> 00:20:14,359
That's the way it is...
Right, Fullmetal?

404
00:20:18,959 --> 00:20:21,059
You will more than
likely come across cases

405
00:20:21,092 --> 00:20:23,325
like this again
in the future...

406
00:20:23,359 --> 00:20:26,792
And you may end up having to get
your own hands dirty, as well.

407
00:20:26,825 --> 00:20:29,959
Are you going to shut down
like this every time?

408
00:20:29,992 --> 00:20:32,325
[Ed] We may be called
dogs of the military...

409
00:20:32,359 --> 00:20:35,992
We may even be cursed as
devils... It doesn't matter.

410
00:20:36,025 --> 00:20:39,025
Al and I are still going
to get our bodies back.

411
00:20:39,059 --> 00:20:43,392
We know the truth.
We know we're not devils.

412
00:20:43,425 --> 00:20:46,559
We know we're not gods!

413
00:20:46,592 --> 00:20:48,225
We're human.

414
00:20:49,859 --> 00:20:52,859
[shouting]
We're only human!

415
00:20:55,325 --> 00:20:58,759
We can't even do anything to
save one innocent little girl.

416
00:21:00,225 --> 00:21:03,225
[Ed] So what good are we, then?

417
00:21:04,359 --> 00:21:08,459
I wonder why no one's
capable of understanding me.

418
00:21:08,492 --> 00:21:10,492
Nina.

419
00:21:11,092 --> 00:21:13,092
[footsteps]

420
00:21:13,825 --> 00:21:16,292
[thunder]

421
00:21:16,325 --> 00:21:18,392
You're Shou Tucker, correct?

422
00:21:18,425 --> 00:21:21,492
Who are you?
Not military...

423
00:21:21,525 --> 00:21:23,392
Who are you?!

424
00:21:23,425 --> 00:21:24,825
How did you get in here?

425
00:21:24,859 --> 00:21:27,792
There were military
police out front!

426
00:21:27,825 --> 00:21:29,925
Foolish alchemists
who turn their backs

427
00:21:29,959 --> 00:21:31,492
on the ways of God...

428
00:21:33,492 --> 00:21:35,492
...shall be punished.

429
00:21:43,559 --> 00:21:45,759
Daddy's hurting.

430
00:21:47,525 --> 00:21:52,392
Daddy hurts... No, Daddy.

431
00:21:52,425 --> 00:21:55,359
You poor creature. Once you
have been given this form,

432
00:21:55,392 --> 00:21:58,059
there is no way of
separating you again.

433
00:21:59,259 --> 00:22:02,459
At least...
Your passing will be in peace.

434
00:22:02,492 --> 00:22:04,092
[thunder]

435
00:22:08,359 --> 00:22:11,092
[Scar] God...

436
00:22:11,125 --> 00:22:15,392
Hear me... Two human souls
have just been returned to you.

437
00:22:15,425 --> 00:22:18,325
Please accept them
into your loving arms.

438
00:22:18,359 --> 00:22:20,792
Please grant these
poor, lost souls

439
00:22:20,825 --> 00:22:23,159
everlasting peace
and salvation.

440
00:24:04,825 --> 00:24:07,825
<i>[Narrator] The rain pours</i>
<i>down in East City.</i>

441
00:24:07,859 --> 00:24:10,192
<i>Still grief-stricken</i>
<i>over the death of Nina...</i>

442
00:24:10,225 --> 00:24:14,192
<i>Ed and Al are attacked by</i>
<i>the mysterious man, Scar.</i>

443
00:24:14,225 --> 00:24:17,192
In a moment of crisis, Ed
must make a desperate decision,

444
00:24:17,225 --> 00:24:20,325
<i>while the life of his brother</i>
<i>hangs in the balance.</i>

445
00:24:20,359 --> 00:24:23,359
<i>Next time, on Fullmetal</i>
<i>Alchemist: Brotherhood--</i>

446
00:24:23,392 --> 00:24:27,159
<i>Episode Five. Rain of Sorrows.</i>

447
00:24:27,192 --> 00:24:29,325
<i>What will Edward decide?</i>

448
00:24:29,359 --> 00:24:32,959
<i>And will he be able to live</i>
<i>with the consequences?</i>

